<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1683,1997]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
REMARKS.—The specimen is the first I have seen with a green pronotal collar, lateral mesonotum and lateral abdominal segment 9. The markings in the mesonotal sigillae are also highly developed. It is a tawny species marked with piceous, the abdominal pile forma n arch on the dorsal surface. The generic characters will also distinguish the lone species represented in 
<collectingCountry box="[404,499,1791,1817]" name="Ecuador" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
